<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1916-05-08T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1916-05-08T00:00:00-05:00" n="534" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d534">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">763.72/2662</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">President <persName type="from">Wilson</persName> to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1916-05-08">
                                    <hi rend="italic">8 May, 1916</hi>.</date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">My Dear Mr. Secretary</hi>: You are probably right
                            about cutting out all “satisfaction”, and I am quite content to have the
                            note go as you have amended it. I am returning it so that it may be sent
                            at once.</p>
                        <p>In haste,</p>
                        <p>Faithfully Yours,</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>W. W.</signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>